                            <comment id="289227" author="pjones" created="Mon, 11 Jan 2021 18:52:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Mike. James will look into making that change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="289174" author="tappro" created="Mon, 11 Jan 2021 08:52:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tend to think this is test script issue, the llog read from client sends RPC to server and &lt;tt&gt;ptlrpc_wait_queue()&lt;/tt&gt; may ends up with &lt;tt&gt;-ESHUTDOWN&lt;/tt&gt; on umount, so that is OK I&apos;d say. Originally this test 160j was added in context of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11626&quot; title=&quot;mdc: obd might go away while referenced by code in mdc_changelog&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11626&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11626&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to check there is no LBUG due to missed obd device so correctness of this test is not about &apos;changelog must be read after umount&apos; but about the server shouldn&apos;t see LBUG during that. Therefore I think we should just consider that error as valid case during the test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="288593" author="jhammond" created="Mon, 4 Jan 2021 18:42:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The first failure I could find with this error message was &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/57f6774c-e2bb-11e9-9874-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/57f6774c-e2bb-11e9-9874-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
